But if one have sworn contrary to a former Oath, he may pretend;


That he was forced.

That he was deceived, and that nether of these is Perjury, since Perjury is voluntary.

But if the Adversary do so, he may say;
That he that stands not to what he hath sworn, subverteth humane society.
